reviews_data.review_text:
I'm in town for a wedding and I'm so glad I tried this place. For breakfast, I had the bacon, egg, and cheese croissant with breakfast potatoes. The food was fresh and delicious.

So, I went back for lunch. I got the grilled chicken Caesar wrap and side salad. 😋😋
Great atmosphere and incredible beignets!!

Good place but they have to figure out parking situation, There is absolutely no onsite parking. 5-6 spots a little down the road are always full due to all the hotels in the area. I have myself turned back 3-4 times just due to lack of parking. For me, if I want enjoy a place i don’t like spending hours finding a parking spot. Then the excitement for me is gone.
One thing I can do is park at Harries teeter or southpark mall and then walk here,
1. thats not fair for those businesses they will loose the spots
2. With a 20 month old toddler it is not easy to always walk 2-3 blocks to eat
I hope this help’s others who are planning to visit this place and don’t live around it.
Fun,  hip spot for a meal,  a drink,  some coffee.  We go to play mahjong.
Friendly service and excellent espresso drinks.
food & staff are always on point!
Really enjoyed lunch at Gourmand Market! The tomato basil soup was so good and they brought us a surprise treat at the bar. Staff was extremely friendly and helpful.

This market offers a comfortable dining environment. The espresso, made with Nightswim beans, provided a standard experience. The deli primarily features Boar's Head meats. The overall atmosphere seems designed for those who wish to enjoy a meal on-site rather than those seeking a quick grab-and-go.

I stopped here the other day to check it out but they were closed so I left within 10 minutes. What's worse is that, despite claiming parking was free for the first three hours, I was charged anyways. This is the 2nd time and 2nd property where I've been ripped off by the parking management company that runs the deck for Gourmand and I regrettably will not return, if I have to face unknown parking fees because their systems fail to properly capture the time of vehicle exits. Another place that uses this company sent me a $200 bill just for passing through their parking lot. So be cautious about parking here folks.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Miriam,
Thank you so much for making the effort to visit - I hate you came on day we are closed. I can also commiserate on the parking garage - it’s been a challenge since we moved in and I wish we had more control over it! Unfortunately, we are at the mercy of the parking company and can't do anything about it. The first 3 hours are definitely free - just make sure you have downloaded the correct app for Metropolis.
Please don’t let this deter you from returning because I would love to introduce myself and pick your brain about solutions - I genuinely appreciate the feedback!

reviews_data.review_text: Gourmand Mkt in SouthPark, Charlotte, is an absolute gem. It’s the cutest little market tucked in the ground floor of an apartment building neighborhood, where you can shop for specialty goods and grab a bite. I sat in there and worked for a few hours. The vibe is stylish but cozy, and their charcuterie board was just perfect. Very good blue cheese. Whether you’re stocking up on gourmet finds or just hanging out, this place is a must-visit. Loved it!
Very fun spot with great drinks and staff. This spot is perfect to relax at on the weekends or after work
Great food, great service, and the beignets were otherworldly

I was thoroughly impressed by Gourmands in South Park, NC—a true culinary gem that masterfully combines ambiance, flavor, and exceptional service.

From the moment we stepped in, the atmosphere was warm and inviting, setting the perfect tone for an exquisite dining experience. We began with the hummus appetizer, which was nothing short of exceptional. The trio of hummus varieties offered a delightful array of flavors, complemented by perfectly crisp pita chips with a buttery undertone that elevated the dish.

For my entrée, I indulged in the burger and fries—a classic done to perfection. The burger was cooked impeccably, bursting with rich, juicy flavor, while the pencil fries were flawlessly seasoned, offering just the right amount of crispness and taste. My husband opted for the steak and cheese sandwich with caramelized onions and fries, and it was an absolute standout. The sandwich was melt-in-your-mouth delicious, with the sweet, perfectly caramelized onions adding a luscious depth of flavor.

We chose to sit at the bar, where the staff impressed us with their professionalism, friendliness, and spot-on recommendations. Their warm conversation and attentiveness enhanced the overall experience. Our food arrived hot and promptly, further showcasing the restaurant's commitment to quality.

Adding to the charm of Gourmands is their gourmet store, brimming with specialty items and premade meals that looked irresistibly tempting—a delightful bonus for food enthusiasts.

Gourmands is a must-visit for anyone in South Park. We cannot wait to return and highly recommend this fantastic spot to others seeking an exceptional dining experience.
Great service!

Stopped in mid morning with a couple of friends.  Two coffees - delicious.  Nightswim coffee beans.  One friend had loose leaf tea served and a press which kept it warm.  Shared an order of beignets - delish.  Great vibe.  Will be back
Loved the entire experience! Festive and great atmosphere!!
Wrap w/Truffle extra BBQ on side 👌🏾

Fire place is toasty, the foods amazing, it’s feels so cozy to have a neighborhood gem, the most polite staff that feels like family!  And many unique things to try! Oh and the coffee, you might not miss Starbucks 😉
Excellent coffee shop with easy access to parking in South Park area

I love this place, my husband and I went there for a bite and I had tons of food allergies but my server/bartender tends to me and helped me make changes to my wrap, she was really above and beyond!~ I’m so sorry I forgot her name but she has a pet cat and we are cat people too!

It is so beautiful and cozy inside, love the mix of black and gold.  The variety of food and snacks there were so unique, I wish there were more places like Gourmand! Very cool experience that I don’t get from anywhere.

Service was excellent! I sat at the bar to have breakfast and the bartender was fabulous! The food was perfect in portions, flavor, and price. The dessert was a cranberry bread pudding with a scoop of vanilla ice cream. I’ll be back!!

Decided to come here on Sunday morning and had the best bloody mary($8 Sunday special!) and the best egg, bacon and and cheese english muffin!  And the most delicious melt-in-your-mouth beignets we’ve ever had!   Such a great concept of modern wine bar, coffee shop, and gourmet market.  the atmosphere is lovely!  Our bartender, Julia, was wonderful!  We loved her friendly, professional and engaging personality!  We will be coming back soon!
Great breakfast sandwich and bloody mary’s! Julia was amazing and very friendly!
Fun place, the baked goods are fantastic. Very eclectic place.
Delicious espresso!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We’re happy to hear it, George! Nothing like a good espresso. We hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Gourmand is a wonderful place to unwind with a glass of wine, appetizers, and a charcuterie board. My husband and I went for a date, and we loved the vibe. There is a wonderful food market inside, along with a bar and coffee station! Their baked goods look amazing. Service staff is super friendly and quick. 100% recommend!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We’re so glad you enjoyed your experience with us! Thank you for the great feedback. We hope to see you for another date night again soon, Ally!

reviews_data.review_text:
Gourmand owner had the decency to reply to my post and admitted to an early, erroneous release on their website about All Day Brunch. I like when people admit their mistakes. I make mistakes all the time. Now I am excited to try their All Day Brunch that launches in August.

I still feel that one employee was a smug jerk when I pointed out the website error, but I won't hold that grudge to my own detriment as Gourmand is AWESOME!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We are sorry for the confusion- we are launching all day brunch in August and posted too early to the website! Please email us at inquiries@gourmandmkt.com so we can make it right!

reviews_data.review_text: Overpriced, weird decorations, and the bartender just makes weird conversation. Dead on a Saturday night. The actual market is somewhat bizarre with everything from CBD to wagyu steak.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Kevin- thank you for your feedback. While we are glad you were able to come in, we know we aren't everyone’s cup of tea! We offer a unique blend of boutique offerings requested by our patrons. We have a wide variety of meals and retail amenities - both take and bake and bar side dining - we hope to see you again!

reviews_data.review_text:
This review is more about service than substance. Shopped a massive order for this company, over $2000, mentioned to the owner Bo Prior to the order that we are compensated by gratuity, as a service industry expert she should know that… I wasted four hours of my time As she only tipped 2.17% of the order total… Would expect more as someone that knows or should know the hospitality business…. Very disappointed. Hopefully she reads this and doesn’t put anyone else through that, Really makes you scratch your head at the selfishness, I will be returning the tip she gave me As a reminder for her not to do that again.

UPDATE: I emailed twice (at your request) and not surprised that I have not received a reply from you.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Scott, thank you for bringing this to our attention. We take our vendor relationships seriously, they’re the lifeblood of our business. The management team and I were unaware of this situation and would like to speak to you and make things right. Please reach out to inquiries@gourmandmkt.com, so we can help assist you.

Update: Hi, Scott. Apologies for the email issue and not receiving them. The email address here has been fixed!

reviews_data.review_text: Their food, drinks, and coffee are all amazing. They always have the most nostalgic snacks and fun gourmet gifts! The staff is super friendly and always very welcoming. Great place for a date night or to sit outside for lunch.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you, Katherine! We’re so happy you enjoyed your experience with us. We hope to see you again soon for lunch or a date night!

reviews_data.review_text: Got to personally sit down with the owner outside today after I ate and talk to her for an hour. She was awesome. Will be back very soon!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Phil, it was great to meet you! We look forward to seeing you again!

reviews_data.review_text: I went there for Birthday party and we all had the best time. The server Sydney did a fantastic job. Eric and Adam were the management and also super helpful. Thank you for making the night so special for my friend’s Birthday.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for joining us, Amber! We appreciate the feedback and are so glad you enjoyed your experience with us. We look forward to seeing you all again!

reviews_data.review_text: Went for Latte on a Saturday afternoon.  Great service and a cozy place! We will come again. 🧡
reviews_data.owner_answer: We appreciate the review, Selam! We look forward to seeing you again!

reviews_data.review_text: This place is amazing! Great food, great service and great layout. You can shop, eat, drink, chill, watch tv. “Bougie but Casual”.

Stopped by to get a coffee after most places nearby are closed. Was pleasantly surprised to find they use Nightswim beans and had a full espresso bar. Not only was the coffee good but the service from the barista, Eric, was fantastic! I plan to stop by next time I am near the SouthPark area.

Can't say enough good things about this place. It's a little different than what you might be expecting. It's a market with a bar to start with. You have a choice of picking food tapas style and they will prepare it fresh or you can take it home and they will teach you how to prepare it. The place is SUPER clean and that's my key factor, always. The food is super fresh and baked items are insanely good. The pastry's are to die for.

This place is a special treat for the Charlotte area!!! Went for there Valentine's special dinner and had an amazing time. The staff,food,drinks and atmosphere were absolutely amazing... great job. I was in the restaurant/bar business for 20 yrs and this is how it is done.

I had to come back and change my review… I hate doing this but as someone who worked in the restaurant industry for years… it was extremely disappointing to return to this bar and deal with the dark haired female bartender tonight. She was literally seething and meaner than a snake for no apparent reason. It was so bad that I had to flat out ask her if she was upset or if we had somehow offended her. This type of service will literally RUIN a place like this that is very niche and in a hard to find location. My friend and I started to feel so uncomfortable that we paid, tipped our 20% and left… it was THAT bad. I won’t be returning!!

Beautiful place, Beautiful people.. delicious food!

Eric and the rest of the staff were memorable. Truly one of our favorite spots in the Southpark area
The food and deserts are amazing. The customer service is top notch. Highly recommend to check it out! Hidden gem

We had the most perfect evening at Gourmand.   The cocktails were  unique and the food was amazing.   Service was great.. The atmosphere was however, my favorite. You’re in an upscale deli/market/wine bar with a fabulous bar. You can choose your steaks and take home to cook or they will cook them for you.   Great evening.  A highlight to our Christmas dining.

Very cool place. We came on a Sunday which only serves breakfast all day and their grab n go, but no biggie.
We ordered regular latte and chai latte, cake, and cookie. The new girl at the coffee area (11/19) was very kind and helpful and made delicious drinks, service all around is very good. We will come back another time during the week/Saturday to try other menu items. Definitely worth a try!

It's a nice place. The staff is limited but pleasant. I had the Cubano sandwich, which came with homemade chips. I asked for some blue cheese dressing to dip the chips in, making this dish a hit. My wife had the Roasted Apple Burrata salad. I tried this and it was my favorite of the two dishes. We tried a couple of their cocktails, the Swwet Potato Pie which was just right for me and the Cheating on Vodka which was fine too. The limited seating is all tall barstools. I am happy we got to try this place.

Absolutely beautiful and bright space. Appropriate for a business meetup, coffee, cocktails. Incredible deli items including house cured Faroe Island smoked salmon, fine aged steaks and other meat cuts, smoked chicken salad, vegan friendly beet hummus and falafel. Warm and friendly staff. Can’t miss the gorgeous black sparkling clean bar with large TVs in case you want to catch the game. Parking is easy and free in the attached deck.

The sandwiches are okay. Not worth the price point they’re selling them at. Might as well go to a legit sandwich shop if that’s what you’re looking for. Not high quality like you would expect for the price.
Amazing drinks & great food in an upscale, unique, and relaxed atmosphere. Can’t wait to go back.

Amazing market and cafe. Food is stellar/fresh/well thought out. Pre prepared meals and take away food are great. Fresh. Quality. Healthy. Yummy.

Fantastic staff and leadership team. You can feel their love of the place. Def worth checking out.  Fantastic original cocktails.

Food menu interesting. Great coffee bar. Bakery items and fresh gourmet choices. Prices reasonable. Comfortable spot. They are new and growing into their righteous place here. This place is an amazing and accommodating keeper. Southpark is lucky to have.  👍🏼

✨Having High Standards for coffee, food, great service and novel experiences I must say that Gourmand checks ✔️ all the boxes!!!!

✨The owner and her team have amazing energy and hospitality!

This is hands down 👇 the best place in Charlotte!!!! ☕🔥👑
Our server Hunter was great and the food was delicious!!
Food was amazing very very good must try if you in Charlotte

An unusual concept for specialty foods.
Feels  like you are in a wine bar.
Meat case looks very good!
Not sure what to order. Is this also a deli?
Can you order if it is not on the menu?
I was curious to see the place.
Espresso was very good!

This place has so much! Small plates, grab and go lunches, take home meals, fresh cut steaks, coffee & liquor bar, etc! The list goes on. Everything is amazing. Staff is so friendly and helpful. Highly recommend!
What an experience… 5 ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

I recently read an article in Charlotte Five about a new concept market/dining establishment in South Park – The Gourmand Market.

Taste France Magazine defines “gourmand” variously as: "A gourmand is similar to what Americans would call a foodie, but on a more gastronomic scale. A gourmand is someone who loves and appreciates good food and wine, and the company that comes along with it."; or, “…a gourmand is someone you want to have around — unlike the modern foodie, who will rattle off ten new sorta-healthy brunch places, the gourmand will lead you to the one century-old bistro that you'll never forget.”

As for me, after having lunch and doing a bit of shopping there today, I would say that The Gourmand Market is a place that I will return to often.

My wife and I wandered in and began to roam the market portion of the place and were immediately greeted by the staff in a friendly and welcoming manner.

We sat at the bar and each ordered a Redwood cocktail which was made with a Woodford Reserve base and a couple of other additions that made the cocktail quite summery and very refreshing.

Sydney took care of us at the bar and was a delight.  She took the time to give us a bit of background on the place and walked us through the etiquette of how to order, etc. as the market/bar/restaurant concept was unfamiliar to us.

While we awaited our sandwiches, we wandered the store, noting all the enticing offerings; pre-made meals, a meat counter, a wide selection of wines, pastries, and various types of specialty foods.  We also explored an upstairs lounge which would be a nice place to sit with friends and enjoy cocktails, small plates, etc.

We decided to have lunch and were quite pleased with the experience.  My wife had a Cubano sandwich and a small side salad and I had a Beef on Weck sandwich with house made chips.

Both sandwiches were excellent.  The Cubano was on crunchy Cuban bread and the pork was quite flavorful.  The Beef on Weck was the equal of any made in Buffalo – the beef was melt-in-your-mouth delicious and the au jus was hearty and flavorful.  I wasn’t shy in my addition of au jus and the Weck quickly absorbed the excess and I was treated to even more intense flavor.  The house cut chips were magnificent – well-seasoned and crunchy.

Once we finished lunch, we selected a few things from the market to take with us – a lasagna, some pasta sauce, and a couple of wonderful coffees for the ride home.

I’m not sure when we will head there next, but breakfast would be a good bet.  There’s nothing quite like sitting with a good cup of coffee (of which there are many types and flavors) and some beignets.  Or, perhaps, a nice croissant or pain au chocolat.  While we did not taste these on this visit, having recently returned from Paris, I was surprised at how close they looked to those we purchased at the local patisserie in Paris.

In short, we were thrilled with our experience at The Gourmand Market.  The staff were top-notch.  Kudos to Sydney for her helpful and friendly service; to Jay, the Executive Chef whose kitchen prepared the meal; and to Yuri, the General Manager who checked us out and made the wonderful coffees.  Also, my apologies for being unable to recall the young man’s name who prepared the salad and brought us our lunches.
Great food and quality items. Service was excellent. We will definitely be back

Welcome to the neighborhood Gourmand, this is an upscale bodega if you will, a bodega with a butcher, prepared foods, coffee, wine and cocktails. Count me in. They have outdoor seating, a lounge area upstairs and bar seating with outlets. If you want to have a cocktail and charge your phone this is the place! What I liked most about this spot, there is a huge wall with  wine fridges, set at proper temperatures. So no 72 degree, room temp red wines and the Champagne fridge was set at the proper temperature, yes, I can see coming here in the afternoon for a small bite and a glass of wine. In the display case they had hand cut ribeyes, hamburger patties, pork chops and flank steak, the prices were reasonable. There's a lot going on in Gourmand, give yourself enough time to take it all in.

What an experience… 5 ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

I recently read an article in Charlotte Five about a new concept market/dining establishment in South Park – The Gourmand Market.

Taste France Magazine defines “gourmand” variously as: "A gourmand is similar to what Americans would call a foodie, but on a more gastronomic scale. A gourmand is someone who loves and appreciates good food and wine, and the company that comes along with it."; or, “…a gourmand is someone you want to have around — unlike the modern foodie, who will rattle off ten new sorta-healthy brunch places, the gourmand will lead you to the one century-old bistro that you'll never forget.”

As for me, after having lunch and doing a bit of shopping there today, I would say that The Gourmand Market is a place that I will return to often.

My wife and I wandered in and began to roam the market portion of the place and were immediately greeted by the staff in a friendly and welcoming manner.

We sat at the bar and each ordered a Redwood cocktail which was made with a Woodford Reserve base and a couple of other additions that made the cocktail quite summery and very refreshing.

Sydney took care of us at the bar and was a delight.  She took the time to give us a bit of background on the place and walked us through the etiquette of how to order, etc. as the market/bar/restaurant concept was unfamiliar to us.

While we awaited our sandwiches, we wandered the store, noting all the enticing offerings; pre-made meals, a meat counter, a wide selection of wines, pastries, and various types of specialty foods.  We also explored an upstairs lounge which would be a nice place to sit with friends and enjoy cocktails, small plates, etc.

We decided to have lunch and were quite pleased with the experience.  My wife had a Cubano sandwich and a small side salad and I had a Beef on Weck sandwich with house made chips.

Both sandwiches were excellent.  The Cubano was on crunchy Cuban bread and the pork was quite flavorful.  The Beef on Weck was the equal of any made in Buffalo – the beef was melt-in-your-mouth delicious and the au jus was hearty and flavorful.  I wasn’t shy in my addition of au jus and the Weck quickly absorbed the excess and I was treated to even more intense flavor.  The house cut chips were magnificent – well-seasoned and crunchy.

Once we finished lunch, we selected a few things from the market to take with us – a lasagna, some pasta sauce, and a couple of wonderful coffees for the ride home.

I’m not sure when we will head there next, but breakfast would be a good bet.  There’s nothing quite like sitting with a good cup of coffee (of which there are many types and flavors) and some beignets.  Or, perhaps, a nice croissant or pain au chocolat.  While we did not taste these on this visit, having recently returned from Paris, I was surprised at how close they looked to those we purchased at the local patisserie in Paris.

In short, we were thrilled with our experience at The Gourmand Market.  The staff were top-notch.  Kudos to Sydney for her helpful and friendly service; to Jay, the Executive Chef whose kitchen prepared the meal; and to Yuri, the General Manager who checked us out and made the wonderful coffees.  Also, my apologies for being unable to recall the young man’s name who prepared the salad and brought us our lunches.
Great food and quality items. Service was excellent. We will definitely be back

Welcome to the neighborhood Gourmand, this is an upscale bodega if you will, a bodega with a butcher, prepared foods, coffee, wine and cocktails. Count me in. They have outdoor seating, a lounge area upstairs and bar seating with outlets. If you want to have a cocktail and charge your phone this is the place! What I liked most about this spot, there is a huge wall with  wine fridges, set at proper temperatures. So no 72 degree, room temp red wines and the Champagne fridge was set at the proper temperature, yes, I can see coming here in the afternoon for a small bite and a glass of wine. In the display case they had hand cut ribeyes, hamburger patties, pork chops and flank steak, the prices were reasonable. There's a lot going on in Gourmand, give yourself enough time to take it all in.
